foreign trade university (ftu) is a university established in 1960, located in hanoi, vietnam. the university also has campuses in ho chi minh city and quáº£ng ninh. ftu is among the most well-known universities in vietnam, covering a wide range of areas - from economics and business to law and foreign languages. students from ftu are recognized as being active and well-qualified. it offers both undergraduate and graduate programs for both local and foreign students. these courses are taught in vietnamese, english, japanese and french.